{
  "texts": [
    "Weizheng LU et al.",
    "Large language model for table processing: a survey 5.3.1 Table QA and NL2SQL For tasks like table QA and NL2SQL, agent systems usually utilize Python or SQL to interact with tables.",
    "In Binder [30], actions are categorized into two types: extended Python and SQL, which allow the injection of LLM as operators within standard Python and SQL.",
    "ReAcTable [15] incorporates three kinds of actions: (1) generating a SQL query, (2) generating Python code, and (3) directly answering the question.",
    "It extends the ReAct framework with an observation-actionreflection loop specifically for table tasks."
  ]
}